Title: Coding The Road Runner Loop Meme
Description: There’s a programming meme featuring the Looney Tunes characters of Wile E. Coyote and the Road Runner. These characters are locked in a never-ending chase, where the Coyote seems to come close, but not quite catch the speedy bird. In the meme itself, it shows the Coyote running off of a cliff due to his misuse of the do / while iteration construct, whereas the Road Runner stops short because he presumably used the while iteration construct.
